The Slovak unit of U.S. Steel plans
to cut 1,655 jobs by 2015,  Sme  reported, citing trade union
leader Mikulas Hintos.  The steelmaker currently employs about 13,000 people,
according to the newspaper. The company plans to cut the
workforce by not replacing quitting or retiring workers, Sme
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
